### Test HTTP Request File for Tree-sitter Grammar Validation

### Simple GET request
GET https://api.example.com/users

### GET request with HTTP version
GET https://api.example.com/users/123 HTTP/1.1

### POST request with headers
POST https://api.example.com/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### POST request with JSON body
POST https://api.example.com/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "age": 30
}

### PUT request with variables in URL
PUT https://api.example.com/users/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane@example.com"
}

### DELETE request
DELETE https://api.example.com/users/123
Authorization: Bearer secret-token

### Request with XML body
POST https://api.example.com/soap
Content-Type: application/xml

<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/">
  <soap:Body>
    <GetUser>
      <userId>123</userId>
    </GetUser>
  </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>

### GraphQL query
POST https://api.example.com/graphql
Content-Type: application/graphql

query GetUser {
  user(id: "123") {
    id
    name
    email
  }
}

### Request with multiple headers
GET https://api.example.com/data
Host: api.example.com
User-Agent: REST-Client/1.0
Accept: application/json
Accept-Encoding: gzip, deflate
Cache-Control: no-cache
Connection: keep-alive

### PATCH request
PATCH https://api.example.com/users/{{id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "active"
}

### OPTIONS request
OPTIONS https://api.example.com/users
Accept: */*

### Request with form data
POST https://api.example.com/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data

file=@document.pdf
description=Test upload

### Request with query parameters in URL
GET https://api.example.com/search?q={{searchTerm}}&limit=10&offset=0
Accept: application/json

### Request with Basic Auth
GET https://api.example.com/protected
Authorization: Basic dXNlcjpwYXNz

# Single line comment test
### GET with comment
GET https://api.example.com/test

// Another comment style
### POST with different comment
POST https://api.example.com/comments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "This is a comment"
}

### Request with empty body separator
POST https://api.example.com/empty
Content-Type: application/json

### Multiple variables in URL and headers
GET https://{{host}}/api/{{version}}/users/{{userId}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Custom-Header: {{customValue}}

### Request with no headers, just body
POST https://api.example.com/simple

{"simple": true}

### HEAD request
HEAD https://api.example.com/resource
Accept: */*

### TRACE request
TRACE https://api.example.com/debug
Max-Forwards: 10

### CONNECT request (for proxies)
CONNECT server.example.com:443 HTTP/1.1
Host: server.example.com:443

